    <p>{`#Amazon EventBridge + PagerDuty Benefits`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`Amazon EventBridge allows teams to easily create event-driven workflows that connect native AWS services with third-party SaaS solutions like PagerDuty.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`With Amazon EventBridge, PagerDuty customers are able to leverage the full breadth of AWS-supported integrations and functionality.`}</li>
    </ul>
    <p>{`#How it Works`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`When a PagerDuty incident is created or updated, an event or webhook can be sent to notify a designated Event Source in your AWS Account and Region. `}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`You can create an Event Bus to retrieve these notifications and deliver them to an AWS target such as Lambda to run a specific function, workflow, SNS topic for another notification delivery, etc. `}</li>
